{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1250,"text":"This will not be a speech"},{"time":2516,"text":"like any one I have ever given."},{"time":5807,"text":"I will talk to you today about"},{"time":9297,"text":"the failure of leadership in global politics"},{"time":14187,"text":"and in our globalizing economy."},{"time":17185,"text":"And I won't provide some feel-good, ready-made solutions."},{"time":24138,"text":"But I will in the end urge you"},{"time":26672,"text":"to rethink, actually take risks, and get involved"},{"time":32115,"text":"in what I see as a global evolution"},{"time":35520,"text":"of democracy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":38330,"text":"Failure of leadership."},{"time":40585,"text":"What is the failure of leadership today?"},{"time":43346,"text":"And why is our democracy not working?"},{"time":46813,"text":"Well, I believe that the failure of leadership is the fact"},{"time":49444,"text":"that we have taken you out of the process."},{"time":53997,"text":"So let me, from my personal experiences,"},{"time":56513,"text":"give you an insight, so that you can step back"},{"time":60742,"text":"and maybe understand why it is so difficult to cope"},{"time":64414,"text":"with the challenges of today and why politics"},{"time":66489,"text":"is going down a blind alley."}]},{"cues":[{"time":70133,"text":"Let's start from the beginning."},{"time":72630,"text":"Let's start from democracy."},{"time":76426,"text":"Well, if you go back to the Ancient Greeks,"},{"time":78451,"text":"it was a revelation, a discovery,"},{"time":81640,"text":"that we had the potential, together,"},{"time":86157,"text":"to be masters of our own fate,"},{"time":89878,"text":"to be able to examine, to learn, to imagine,"},{"time":92750,"text":"and then to design a better life."},{"time":96083,"text":"And democracy was the political innovation"},{"time":101269,"text":"which protected this freedom,"},{"time":103771,"text":"because we were liberated from fear"},{"time":109086,"text":"so that our minds in fact,"},{"time":110739,"text":"whether they be despots or dogmas,"},{"time":113461,"text":"could be the protagonists."},{"time":117864,"text":"Democracy was the political innovation that allowed us"},{"time":120853,"text":"to limit the power, whether it was of tyrants"},{"time":124241,"text":"or of high priests,"},{"time":126988,"text":"their natural tendency to maximize power and wealth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":131826,"text":"Well, I first began to understand this"},{"time":133436,"text":"when I was 14 years old."},{"time":135558,"text":"I used to, to try to avoid homework,"},{"time":137668,"text":"sneak down to the living room and listen to my parents"},{"time":142844,"text":"and their friends debate heatedly."},{"time":144544,"text":"You see, then Greece was"},{"time":146922,"text":"under control of a very powerful establishment"},{"time":151159,"text":"which was strangling the country,"},{"time":152906,"text":"and my father was heading a promising movement"},{"time":155599,"text":"to reimagine Greece, to imagine a Greece"},{"time":158419,"text":"where freedom reigned and where, maybe,"},{"time":160862,"text":"the people, the citizens, could actually rule their own country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":164573,"text":"I used to join him in many of the campaigns,"},{"time":166869,"text":"and you can see me here next to him."},{"time":168808,"text":"I'm the younger one there, to the side."},{"time":171276,"text":"You may not recognize me because"},{"time":174384,"text":"I used to part my hair differently there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":176612,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":178489,"text":"So in 1967, elections were coming,"},{"time":182636,"text":"things were going well in the campaign,"},{"time":184480,"text":"the house was electric."},{"time":186491,"text":"We really could sense that there was going to be"},{"time":188779,"text":"a major progressive change in Greece."}]},{"cues":[{"time":192776,"text":"Then one night, military trucks drive up to our house."},{"time":197728,"text":"Soldiers storm the door."},{"time":200106,"text":"They find me up on the top terrace."},{"time":204276,"text":"A sergeant comes up to me with a machine gun,"},{"time":206231,"text":"puts it to my head, and says,"},{"time":208190,"text":"\"Tell me where your father is or I will kill you.\""},{"time":212542,"text":"My father, hiding nearby, reveals himself,"},{"time":216724,"text":"and was summarily taken to prison."}]},{"cues":[{"time":220889,"text":"Well, we survived, but democracy did not."},{"time":224625,"text":"Seven brutal years of dictatorship"},{"time":227137,"text":"which we spent in exile."}]},{"cues":[{"time":230929,"text":"Now, today, our democracies are again"},{"time":233153,"text":"facing a moment of truth."},{"time":235432,"text":"Let me tell you a story."},{"time":237259,"text":"Sunday evening,"},{"time":239543,"text":"Brussels, April 2010."},{"time":242662,"text":"I'm sitting with my counterparts in the European Union."},{"time":246215,"text":"I had just been elected prime minister,"},{"time":249698,"text":"but I had the unhappy privilege of revealing a truth"},{"time":253291,"text":"that our deficit was not 6 percent,"},{"time":256712,"text":"as had been officially reported only a few days earlier"},{"time":260258,"text":"before the elections by the previous government,"},{"time":263227,"text":"but actually 15.6 percent."},{"time":268115,"text":"But the deficit was only the symptom"},{"time":270547,"text":"of much deeper problems that Greece was facing,"},{"time":272863,"text":"and I had been elected on a mandate, a mission, actually,"},{"time":276794,"text":"to tackle these problems,"},{"time":278039,"text":"whether it was lack of transparency"},{"time":280773,"text":"and accountability in governance,"},{"time":283074,"text":"or whether it was a clientelistic state"},{"time":285740,"text":"offering favors to the powerful -- tax avoidance"},{"time":290293,"text":"abetted and aided by a global tax evasion system,"},{"time":295020,"text":"politics and media captured by special interests."},{"time":298452,"text":"But despite our electoral mandate,"},{"time":301452,"text":"the markets mistrusted us."},{"time":304667,"text":"Our borrowing costs were skyrocketing,"},{"time":307433,"text":"and we were facing possible default."}]},{"cues":[{"time":310340,"text":"So I went to Brussels on a mission"},{"time":313620,"text":"to make the case for a united European response,"},{"time":317634,"text":"one that would calm the markets and give us the time"},{"time":320934,"text":"to make the necessary reforms."},{"time":323940,"text":"But time we didn't get."},{"time":326844,"text":"Picture yourselves around the table in Brussels."},{"time":329980,"text":"Negotiations are difficult, the tensions are high,"},{"time":332871,"text":"progress is slow, and then, 10 minutes to 2,"},{"time":335748,"text":"a prime minister shouts out,"},{"time":337320,"text":"\"We have to finish in 10 minutes.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":339840,"text":"I said, \"Why? These are important decisions."},{"time":342473,"text":"Let's deliberate a little bit longer.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":344628,"text":"Another prime minister comes in and says,"},{"time":347711,"text":"\"No, we have to have an agreement now,"},{"time":351043,"text":"because in 10 minutes,"},{"time":353395,"text":"the markets are opening up in Japan,"},{"time":356960,"text":"and there will be havoc in the global economy.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":361409,"text":"We quickly came to a decision in those 10 minutes."},{"time":364822,"text":"This time it was not the military,"},{"time":367098,"text":"but the markets, that put a gun to our collective heads."},{"time":373586,"text":"What followed were the most difficult decisions in my life,"},{"time":377769,"text":"painful to me, painful to my countrymen,"},{"time":381996,"text":"imposing cuts, austerity,"},{"time":385018,"text":"often on those not to blame for the crisis."},{"time":388244,"text":"With these sacrifices, Greece did avoid bankruptcy"},{"time":391371,"text":"and the eurozone avoided a collapse."}]},{"cues":[{"time":394523,"text":"Greece, yes, triggered the Euro crisis,"},{"time":397171,"text":"and some people blame me for pulling the trigger."},{"time":400289,"text":"But I think today that most would agree"},{"time":403336,"text":"that Greece was only a symptom"},{"time":405702,"text":"of much deeper structural problems in the eurozone,"},{"time":409379,"text":"vulnerabilities in the wider global economic system,"},{"time":413571,"text":"vulnerabilities of our democracies."},{"time":416217,"text":"Our democracies are trapped by systems too big to fail,"},{"time":420554,"text":"or, more accurately, too big to control."},{"time":423923,"text":"Our democracies are weakened in the global economy"},{"time":426252,"text":"with players that can evade laws, evade taxes,"},{"time":429723,"text":"evade environmental or labor standards."},{"time":433044,"text":"Our democracies are undermined"},{"time":435926,"text":"by the growing inequality"},{"time":438084,"text":"and the growing concentration of power and wealth,"},{"time":441864,"text":"lobbies, corruption, the speed of the markets"},{"time":445518,"text":"or simply the fact that we sometimes fear an impending disaster,"},{"time":450357,"text":"have constrained our democracies,"},{"time":453077,"text":"and they have constrained our capacity"},{"time":455965,"text":"to imagine and actually use the potential, your potential,"},{"time":459963,"text":"in finding solutions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":462478,"text":"Greece, you see, was only a preview"},{"time":464933,"text":"of what is in store for us all."},{"time":467310,"text":"I, overly optimistically, had hoped"},{"time":469000,"text":"that this crisis was an opportunity for Greece, for Europe,"},{"time":472791,"text":"for the world, to make radical democratic transformations"},{"time":477266,"text":"in our institutions."},{"time":479143,"text":"Instead, I had a very humbling experience."},{"time":483040,"text":"In Brussels, when we tried desperately again and again"},{"time":487521,"text":"to find common solutions,"},{"time":489430,"text":"I realized that not one, not one of us,"},{"time":493103,"text":"had ever dealt with a similar crisis."},{"time":496574,"text":"But worse, we were trapped by our collective ignorance."},{"time":500570,"text":"We were led by our fears."},{"time":504038,"text":"And our fears led to a blind faith"},{"time":508591,"text":"in the orthodoxy of austerity."},{"time":511756,"text":"Instead of reaching out to the common"},{"time":515559,"text":"or the collective wisdom in our societies,"},{"time":518939,"text":"investing in it to find more creative solutions,"},{"time":522251,"text":"we reverted to political posturing."},{"time":524811,"text":"And then we were surprised when every"},{"time":526417,"text":"ad hoc new measure didn't bring an end to the crisis,"},{"time":529715,"text":"and of course that made it very easy"},{"time":532644,"text":"to look for a whipping boy"},{"time":534491,"text":"for our collective European failure,"},{"time":536289,"text":"and of course that was Greece."},{"time":539643,"text":"Those profligate, idle, ouzo-swilling, Zorba-dancing Greeks,"},{"time":544815,"text":"they are the problem. Punish them!"},{"time":547880,"text":"Well, a convenient but unfounded stereotype"},{"time":551090,"text":"that sometimes hurt even more than austerity itself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":555823,"text":"But let me warn you, this is not just about Greece."},{"time":559135,"text":"This could be the pattern"},{"time":562087,"text":"that leaders follow again and again"},{"time":564593,"text":"when we deal with these complex, cross-border problems,"},{"time":568255,"text":"whether it's climate change, whether it's migration,"},{"time":571975,"text":"whether it's the financial system."},{"time":575039,"text":"That is, abandoning our collective power"},{"time":577625,"text":"to imagine our potential,"},{"time":579504,"text":"falling victims to our fears, our stereotypes, our dogmas,"},{"time":583683,"text":"taking our citizens out of the process"},{"time":585943,"text":"rather than building the process around our citizens."},{"time":590115,"text":"And doing so will only test the faith"},{"time":592587,"text":"of our citizens, of our peoples, even more"},{"time":594995,"text":"in the democratic process."}]},{"cues":[{"time":597557,"text":"It's no wonder that many political leaders,"},{"time":599255,"text":"and I don't exclude myself,"},{"time":601773,"text":"have lost the trust of our people."},{"time":604851,"text":"When riot police have to protect parliaments,"},{"time":608414,"text":"a scene which is increasingly common around the world,"},{"time":612611,"text":"then there's something deeply wrong with our democracies."},{"time":617361,"text":"That's why I called for a referendum to have the Greek people"},{"time":621266,"text":"own and decide on the terms of the rescue package."},{"time":625502,"text":"My European counterparts, some of them, at least,"},{"time":627405,"text":"said, \"You can't do this."},{"time":629390,"text":"There will be havoc in the markets again.\""},{"time":633938,"text":"I said, \"We need to, before we restore confidence in the markets,"},{"time":638194,"text":"we need to restore confidence and trust amongst our people.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":643782,"text":"Since leaving office, I have had time to reflect."},{"time":646550,"text":"We have weathered the storm, in Greece and in Europe,"},{"time":651670,"text":"but we remain challenged."},{"time":654243,"text":"If politics is the power to imagine and use our potential,"},{"time":657702,"text":"well then 60-percent youth unemployment in Greece,"},{"time":661846,"text":"and in other countries, certainly is a lack of imagination"},{"time":664816,"text":"if not a lack of compassion."},{"time":667282,"text":"So far, we've thrown economics at the problem,"},{"time":669823,"text":"actually mostly austerity,"},{"time":672134,"text":"and certainly we could have designed alternatives,"},{"time":675364,"text":"a different strategy, a green stimulus for green jobs,"},{"time":678686,"text":"or mutualized debt, Eurobonds which would"},{"time":682138,"text":"support countries in need from market pressures,"},{"time":685262,"text":"these would have been much more viable alternatives."},{"time":688134,"text":"Yet I have come to believe that the problem is not so much"},{"time":690800,"text":"one of economics as it is one of democracy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":694759,"text":"So let's try something else."},{"time":696347,"text":"Let's see how we can bring people back to the process."},{"time":699243,"text":"Let's throw democracy at the problem."},{"time":702346,"text":"Again, the Ancient Greeks, with all their shortcomings,"},{"time":705331,"text":"believed in the wisdom of the crowd"},{"time":708375,"text":"at their best moments. In people we trust."},{"time":711266,"text":"Democracy could not work without the citizens"},{"time":714609,"text":"deliberating, debating, taking on public responsibilities"},{"time":718982,"text":"for public affairs."},{"time":720916,"text":"Average citizens often were chosen for citizen juries"},{"time":723650,"text":"to decide on critical matters of the day."},{"time":727877,"text":"Science, theater, research, philosophy,"},{"time":730954,"text":"games of the mind and the body,"},{"time":733037,"text":"they were daily exercises."},{"time":734765,"text":"Actually they were an education for participation,"},{"time":738917,"text":"for the potential, for growing the potential of our citizens."}]},{"cues":[{"time":742457,"text":"And those who shunned politics, well, they were idiots."},{"time":746993,"text":"You see, in Ancient Greece, in ancient Athens,"},{"time":750237,"text":"that term originated there."},{"time":752508,"text":"\"Idiot\" comes from the root \"idio,\" oneself."},{"time":757301,"text":"A person who is self-centered, secluded, excluded,"},{"time":760544,"text":"someone who doesn't participate or even examine public affairs."},{"time":765259,"text":"And participation took place in the agora, the agora having two meanings,"},{"time":768991,"text":"both a marketplace and a place where there was political deliberation."},{"time":775368,"text":"You see, markets and politics then were one, unified,"},{"time":779424,"text":"accessible, transparent, because they gave power to the people."},{"time":782630,"text":"They serve the demos, democracy."},{"time":787593,"text":"Above government, above markets"},{"time":790217,"text":"was the direct rule of the people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":792746,"text":"Today we have globalized the markets"},{"time":795730,"text":"but we have not globalized our democratic institutions."},{"time":800193,"text":"So our politicians are limited to local politics,"},{"time":804626,"text":"while our citizens, even though they see a great potential,"},{"time":808386,"text":"are prey to forces beyond their control."}]},{"cues":[{"time":812866,"text":"So how then do we reunite the two halves of the agora?"},{"time":815697,"text":"How do we democratize globalization?"},{"time":817937,"text":"And I'm not talking about the necessary reforms"},{"time":820506,"text":"of the United Nations or the G20."},{"time":823160,"text":"I'm talking about, how do we secure the space,"},{"time":825641,"text":"the demos, the platform of values,"},{"time":828142,"text":"so that we can tap into all of your potential?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":833702,"text":"Well, this is exactly where I think Europe fits in."},{"time":837577,"text":"Europe, despite its recent failures,"},{"time":839977,"text":"is the world's most successful cross-border peace experiment."},{"time":844545,"text":"So let's see if it can't be an experiment"},{"time":847792,"text":"in global democracy, a new kind of democracy."},{"time":851972,"text":"Let's see if we can't design a European agora,"},{"time":855082,"text":"not simply for products and services,"},{"time":857614,"text":"but for our citizens, where they can work together,"},{"time":860857,"text":"deliberate, learn from each other,"},{"time":862620,"text":"exchange between art and cultures,"},{"time":865836,"text":"where they can come up with creative solutions."},{"time":869535,"text":"Let's imagine that European citizens"},{"time":872705,"text":"actually have the power to vote directly"},{"time":874999,"text":"for a European president,"},{"time":877999,"text":"or citizen juries chosen by lottery"},{"time":881483,"text":"which can deliberate on critical and controversial issues,"},{"time":885709,"text":"a European-wide referendum where our citizens,"},{"time":888877,"text":"as the lawmakers, vote on future treaties."},{"time":893279,"text":"And here's an idea:"},{"time":895759,"text":"Why not have the first truly European citizens"},{"time":898683,"text":"by giving our immigrants,"},{"time":900703,"text":"not Greek or German or Swedish citizenship,"},{"time":904815,"text":"but a European citizenship?"},{"time":908438,"text":"And make sure we actually empower"},{"time":911325,"text":"the unemployed by giving them a voucher scholarship"},{"time":914104,"text":"where they can choose to study anywhere in Europe."},{"time":917573,"text":"Where our common identity is democracy,"},{"time":922054,"text":"where our education is through participation,"},{"time":927018,"text":"and where participation builds trust"},{"time":930491,"text":"and solidarity rather than exclusion and xenophobia."},{"time":934462,"text":"Europe of and by the people,"},{"time":936124,"text":"a Europe, an experiment in deepening and widening"},{"time":940222,"text":"democracy beyond borders."}]},{"cues":[{"time":943238,"text":"Now, some might accuse me of being naive,"},{"time":947076,"text":"putting my faith in the power and the wisdom of the people."},{"time":951947,"text":"Well, after decades in politics, I am also a pragmatist."},{"time":956716,"text":"Believe me, I have been,"},{"time":959272,"text":"I am, part of today's political system,"},{"time":962932,"text":"and I know things must change."},{"time":967569,"text":"We must revive politics as the power to imagine,"},{"time":971857,"text":"reimagine, and redesign for a better world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":977080,"text":"But I also know that this disruptive force of change"},{"time":979894,"text":"won't be driven by the politics of today."},{"time":982958,"text":"The revival of democratic politics"},{"time":985254,"text":"will come from you, and I mean all of you."},{"time":989674,"text":"Everyone who participates in this global exchange of ideas,"},{"time":993660,"text":"whether it's here in this room"},{"time":994709,"text":"or just outside this room"},{"time":996922,"text":"or online or locally, where everybody lives,"},{"time":1000756,"text":"everyone who stands up to injustice and inequality,"},{"time":1004076,"text":"everybody who stands up to those who preach"},{"time":1006796,"text":"racism rather than empathy,"},{"time":1009060,"text":"dogma rather than critical thinking,"},{"time":1011876,"text":"technocracy rather than democracy,"},{"time":1014192,"text":"everyone who stands up to the unchecked power,"},{"time":1017167,"text":"whether it's authoritarian leaders,"},{"time":1019288,"text":"plutocrats hiding their assets in tax havens,"},{"time":1022724,"text":"or powerful lobbies protecting the powerful few."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1026644,"text":"It is in their interest that all of us are idiots."},{"time":1032077,"text":"Let's not be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1033563,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1034803,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1046713,"text":"Bruno Giussani: You seem to describe a political leadership"},{"time":1048626,"text":"that is kind of unprepared"},{"time":1050811,"text":"and a prisoner of the whims of the financial markets,"},{"time":1053593,"text":"and that scene in Brussels that you describe, to me,"},{"time":1055953,"text":"as a citizen, is terrifying."},{"time":1058456,"text":"Help us understand how you felt after the decision."},{"time":1062755,"text":"It was not a good decision, clearly,"},{"time":1064323,"text":"but how do you feel after that, not as the prime minister,"},{"time":1066907,"text":"but as George?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1069096,"text":"George Papandreou: Well, obviously there were constraints"},{"time":1071638,"text":"which didn't allow me or others to make"},{"time":1075564,"text":"the types of decisions we would have wanted,"},{"time":1077004,"text":"and obviously I had hoped that we would have the time"},{"time":1079769,"text":"to make the reforms which would have dealt"},{"time":1081476,"text":"with the deficit rather than trying to cut the deficit"},{"time":1083969,"text":"which was the symptom of the problem."},{"time":1085684,"text":"And that hurt. That hurt because that, first of all,"},{"time":1087883,"text":"hurt the younger generation, and not only,"},{"time":1091387,"text":"many of them are demonstrating outside,"},{"time":1093324,"text":"but I think this is one of our problems."},{"time":1094948,"text":"When we face these crises, we have kept the potential,"},{"time":1100180,"text":"the huge potential of our society out of this process,"},{"time":1103315,"text":"and we are closing in on ourselves in politics,"},{"time":1106139,"text":"and I think we need to change that, to really find"},{"time":1108885,"text":"new participatory ways using the great capabilities"},{"time":1113058,"text":"that now exist even in technology but not only in technology,"},{"time":1116208,"text":"the minds that we have, and I think we can find solutions"},{"time":1119349,"text":"which are much better, but we have to be open."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1121156,"text":"BG: You seem to suggest that the way forward"},{"time":1122816,"text":"is more Europe, and that is not to be an easy discourse"},{"time":1126427,"text":"right now in most European countries."},{"time":1128150,"text":"It's rather the other way -- more closed borders"},{"time":1131877,"text":"and less cooperation and maybe even stepping out"},{"time":1134307,"text":"of some of the different parts of the European construction."},{"time":1138012,"text":"How do you reconcile that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1139951,"text":"GP: Well, I think one of the worst things that happened"},{"time":1142380,"text":"during this crisis is that we started a blame game."},{"time":1144612,"text":"And the fundamental idea of Europe is that"},{"time":1148170,"text":"we can cooperate beyond borders,"},{"time":1150276,"text":"go beyond our conflicts and work together."},{"time":1152577,"text":"And the paradox is that, because we have this blame game,"},{"time":1158546,"text":"we have less the potential to convince our citizens"},{"time":1161726,"text":"that we should work together,"},{"time":1163437,"text":"while now is the time when we really need"},{"time":1165510,"text":"to bring our powers together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1167278,"text":"Now, more Europe for me is not simply"},{"time":1170232,"text":"giving more power to Brussels."},{"time":1171687,"text":"It is actually giving more power to the citizens of Europe,"},{"time":1175560,"text":"that is, really making Europe a project of the people."},{"time":1179408,"text":"So that, I think, would be a way to answer"},{"time":1181976,"text":"some of the fears that we have in our society."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1184849,"text":"BG: George, thank you for coming to TED."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1186372,"text":"GP: Thank you very much.BG: Thank you.(Applause)"}]}]}